  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Behavior",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true,
        "uui-richTextEditor-bold": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Progress bar display progress by animating an indicator along the length of a fixed, visible track. The behavior of the indicator is dependent on whether the progress of a process is known.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "When a lot of elements are loading together it’s better to use skeletons. Progress bars can be used for loading some specific element.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Types",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true,
        "uui-richTextEditor-bold": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Progress bar support both determinate and indeterminate operations.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "unordered-list",
    "children": [
      {
        "data": {},
        "type": "list-item",
        "children": [
          {
            "data": {},
            "type": "list-item-child",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Determinate operations display the indicator increasing in width from 0 to 100% of the track, in sync with the process’s progress.",
                "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "data": {},
        "type": "list-item",
        "children": [
          {
            "data": {},
            "type": "list-item-child",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Indeterminate operations display the indicator continually growing and shrinking along the track until the process is complete.",
                "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "For better overview of how to use different types of indicator review section",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": " ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "“determined",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": " ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "and Indetermined”",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Determined progress bar is also divided into simple, percent, stripped and indicator. Simple, percent and stripped progress bar could be used equally depending on what you think will look better.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Indicator CAN ONLY BE USED FOR SHOWING UPLOADING OF PAGE. ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Size of elements",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "There are 3 possible size of loaders to use: large, medium, small.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {
      "src": "http://static.cdn.epam.com/uploads/690afa39a93c88c4dd13758fe1d869d5/EPM-UUI/Images/LOD5.png",
      "imageSize": {
        "width": 934,
        "height": 412.51666666666665
      }
    },
    "type": "image",
    "url": "http://static.cdn.epam.com/uploads/690afa39a93c88c4dd13758fe1d869d5/EPM-UUI/Images/LOD5.png",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ],
    "width": 934
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "The main rule of using appropriate size of element is that their size should be",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": " ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "visually proportional",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true,
        "uui-richTextEditor-bold": true
      },
      {
        "text": " ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "to the element for which it is used.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "So large elements should be basically used for some big elements, such as the whole page or big section.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Medium elements should be used for smaller sections or elements, like cards. But if you have already used a large loader size for a similar type of component, you should choose only one of them and use it everywhere in the system.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Small size elements should logically be used for small components, such as buttons. Use the size option when you need to increase or decrease the visual weight of the loader.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {
      "src": "http://static.cdn.epam.com/uploads/690afa39a93c88c4dd13758fe1d869d5/EPM-UUI/Images/LOD 6.png",
      "imageSize": {
        "width": 934,
        "height": 280.2
      }
    },
    "type": "image",
    "url": "http://static.cdn.epam.com/uploads/690afa39a93c88c4dd13758fe1d869d5/EPM-UUI/Images/LOD 6.png",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ],
    "width": 934
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-2",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Sceletons",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Types",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "There are four types of skeletons: item, text block, person, card. Skeleton page is used with other skeleton loading components to provide a low fidelity representation of the user interface",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": " ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "(UI)",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": " ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "before content appears on the page.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {
      "src": "http://static.cdn.epam.com/uploads/690afa39a93c88c4dd13758fe1d869d5/EPM-UUI/Images/LOD7.png",
      "imageSize": {
        "width": 934,
        "height": 1438.36
      },
      "align": null
    },
    "type": "image",
    "url": "http://static.cdn.epam.com/uploads/690afa39a93c88c4dd13758fe1d869d5/EPM-UUI/Images/LOD7.png",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": ""
      }
    ],
    "width": 934
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Behaviour",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "paragraph",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "On launch, core structural elements – such as the status bar, app bar, and bottom sheet – are displayed without content until the app has loaded. ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "Placeholder elements, with subtle animation, should be displayed in locations where content will load. ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "Use also indicator while loading the page. ",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      },
      {
        "text": "Placeholder elements should remain positioned where content will load to avoid unexpected shifts in positioning.",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
    "children": [
      {
        "text": "Best practices",
        "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "data": {},
    "type": "unordered-list",
    "children": [
      {
        "data": {},
        "type": "list-item",
        "children": [
          {
            "data": {},
            "type": "list-item-child",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Try to match the number of lines of the text block to the content being loaded so it gives an accurate representation.",
                "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "data": {},
        "type": "list-item",
        "children": [
          {
            "data": {},
            "type": "list-item-child",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Show static content that never changes on a page and",
                "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
              },
              {
                "text": " ",
                "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
              },
              {
                "text": "use skeleton loading for dynamic content",
                "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
              },
              {
                "text": ". Skeleton text block can sometimes be used to represent non-typographic content such as forms. Don’t use placeholder content that will change when the page fully loads.",
                "uui-richTextEditor-span-mark": true
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
